You use `anyhow::any()` to unwrap and wrap your existing `Result`. It's a simple macro that takes the error value from the Result and wraps it in an anyhow Result. For example:

```rust
use anyhow::any;

fn insert_user(user: &User) -> anyhow::Result<(), DatabaseError> {
    let db = get_db();
    user.db.insert(&db, &user.user);
    Ok(())
}
```

Now wrap it:
```rust
let result = anyhow::any(insert_user());
```

It doesn't change the internal structure of your error or add its own wrapper metadata—it just wraps *that* value in another one. This keeps your logic transparent while giving you standard anyhow error context.
